'''Alfred Matthew "Weird Al" Yankovic''' (born [[October 23]], [[1950s#1959|1959]]<ref name="This Week Hype" />) is a singer-songwriter known chiefly for his parodies of popular songs, as well as "style parodies" of specific artists or groups. Since [[1976]], he has sold over 12 million albums and recorded over 150 parodies and original songs. His works have gained him three [[Wikipedia:Grammy Award|Grammy Awards]] (out of nine nominations), four [[Wikipedia:RIAA certification|gold records]] and six [[Wikipedia:RIAA certification|platinum records]].

==Biography==
"Weird Al" Yankovic created two ''[[Star Wars]]''&ndash;themed song parodies, "[[Wikipedia:Yoda (song)|Yoda]]" and "[[The Saga Begins (song)|The Saga Begins]]," from his [[Wikipedia:Dare to Be Stupid|''Dare to Be Stupid'']] and [[Wikipedia:Running with Scissors (album)|''Running With Scissors'']] albums respectively. There is also a scene in the video of his hit single "[[Wikipedia:White & Nerdy|White & Nerdy]]" in which Al makes a back-alley purchase of a bootlegged VHS of ''[[The Star Wars Holiday Special]]''.

During [[Wikipedia:The Weird Al Show|''The Weird Al Show'']], Yankovic planned on green-screening himself into scenes from ''Star Wars'', portraying [[Luke Skywalker]]'s "annoying younger brother." Though Yankovic got permission from [[George Lucas]] and Sir [[Alec Guinness]], he did not get permission from [[Mark Hamill]], and thus scrapped the skit.<ref name="Show">{{SWArchive|url=community/news/rocks/news20061027.html|text="Weird Al" -- Nerdy Something}}</ref>

Yankovic wrote music and voiced [[4-LOM]]<ref name="CBR">{{WebCite|url=https://www.cbr.com/star-wars-detours-musical-weird-al-yankovich-songs|text=Weird Al Reveals He Wrote Half a Dozen Songs For a Musical Episode of Star Wars Detours|author=John Dodge|date=2022-03-24|work=[[Wikipedia:Comic Book Resources|''Comic Book Resources'']]|archivedate=20220324173144}}</ref> for [[Seth Green]] and [[Matt Senreich]]'s unreleased animated series, ''[[Star Wars Detours]]'',<ref name="Detours">{{WebCite|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2012/08/24/first-footage-shown-from-seth-green-and-matt-senreichs-star-wars-detours-animated-series|text=First Footage Shown from Seth Green and Matt Senreich's Star Wars: Detours Animated Series|author=Eric Goldman|date=2012-08-24|work=[[Wikipedia:IGN|''IGN'']]|archivedate=20200531000837}}</ref> and later played [[Vic Vankoh]] in ''[[LEGO Star Wars Summer Vacation]]''.<ref name="SWCA 2022">{{SWYouTube|jqcv2RJ83nE|Star Wars Celebration LIVE! - DAY 2}}</ref> In the special, he performed the original song "[[Scarif Beach Party]]."<ref name="Vacation">{{SW|url=news/lego-star-wars-summer-vacation-trailer|text=5 Things We Love About the ''LEGO Star Wars Summer Vacation'' Trailer}}</ref>

